---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
---
<Layout title="research · alan wu" current="research">
  <header class="pt-10 max-w-2xl">
    <h1 class="font-serif text-4xl md:text-5xl tracking-tight">Research</h1>
    <p class="mt-3 text-[var(--color-mute)]">
      Three threads, one through-line: how a small signal (a molecule, a spike,
      a single dot) composes into the much larger behavior of a system.
    </p>
  </header>

  <ul class="mt-12 space-y-12">
    <li>
      <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[var(--color-mute)]">2024 to present · Cornell, Kessler Lab</p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl wake mt-1">Volatile-mediated signaling in <em>Plectranthus</em> and goldenrod</h2>
      <p class="text-[var(--color-mute)] mt-2 max-w-2xl">
        Investigating terpene-based VOC signaling in <em>Plectranthus tomentosa</em>
        (Vicks plant) and goldenrods, and how plants perceive and react to
        environmental cues through purely chemical communication.
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[var(--color-mute)]">May–Aug 2025 · Institute of Biophysics, CAS</p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl wake mt-1">Drosophila whole-brain imaging &amp; circuit analysis</h2>
      <p class="text-[var(--color-mute)] mt-2 max-w-2xl">
        Whole-brain Drosophila imaging using light-sheet and functional imaging.
        Built image-registration pipelines to align large-scale brain datasets,
        and ran pathway-level analysis on circuits underlying protein-feeding
        behavior and metabolic regulation.
      </p>
    </li>

    <li>
      <p class="font-mono text-xs uppercase tracking-[0.2em] text-[var(--color-mute)]">2023 · University of Chicago, Daou Lab</p>
      <h2 class="font-serif text-2xl wake mt-1">Hippocampal pyramidal-cell plasticity in Parkinson's</h2>
      <p class="text-[var(--color-mute)] mt-2 max-w-2xl">
        Built Python pipelines to extract features from patch-clamp recordings,
        identifying Na⁺ ion-channel malfunction in hippocampal pyramidal cells
        and proposing therapeutic directions.
        <br/>
        Accepted at ICMMGH 2024 and published in <em>Theoretical and Natural Science (TNS)</em>.
      </p>
    </li>
  </ul>
</Layout>
